            <title>[SPARK-21369] Don&apos;t use Scala classes in external shuffle service</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21369</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now the external shuffle service uses Scala Tuple2. However, the Scala library won&apos;t be shaded into the yarn shuffle assembly jar. Then when the codes are called, it will throw ClassNotFoundException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right now it&apos;s safe because we disabled spark.reducer.maxReqSizeShuffleToMem by default. However,  to allow using spark.reducer.maxReqSizeShuffleToMem for Yarn users, we should remove all usages of Tuples.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
